    What is a hydrate shampoo?
    An AI Overview is not available for this searchCan't generate an AI overview right now. Try again later.
    AI Overview
    Hydrating shampoo is a type of shampoo formulated to add moisture to dry or dehydrated hair. It's designed to replenish moisture, leaving hair feeling softer, smoother, and more manageable. These shampoos often contain ingredients that attract and retain moisture, like humectants, and may also include nourishing oils and vitamins. 
    Here's a more detailed explanation:
    • Purpose:
      Hydrating shampoos aim to address dryness and lack of moisture in the hair. 
    • Key Ingredients:
      Look for ingredients like humectants (which attract and retain moisture), nourishing oils (like argan, coconut, or avocado oil), and moisturizing agents (like aloe vera, hyaluronic acid, or ceramides). 
    • Benefits:
      Hydrating shampoos can improve hair's softness, smoothness, shine, and manageability. 
    • Who Benefits:
      They are particularly helpful for those with dry, frizzy, or color-treated hair, as well as those with curly hair, which tends to be naturally drier, according to Sephora Canada and www.shanti.world. 
    • Hydration vs. Moisture:
      While "hydrating" and "moisturizing" are sometimes used interchangeably, hydration generally refers to adding water to the hair, while moisturizing focuses on locking in that moisture. 
    • When to Use:
      If your hair feels dry, dull, or lacks shine, a hydrating shampoo can be a beneficial addition to your routine, says Sephora Canada.
